name: Tattoo balms
description:
BLOODBATH:
100% natural balm created to heal your newly tattooed flesh better than any other. Made from only the finest organic oils known for their natural ability to heal and moisturize. Fast absorbing and packaged in a handy pocket size slider tin.Throw away that sticky ointment you have sitting in the cabinet and try this, you won't be sorry you did. 
Emu Oil- Known for its extraordinary ability to deeply penetrate and heal, reduce inflammation and redness and restore moisture to irritated, dry flesh. It is widely used to heal burns and scars, as it prevents the formation of scar tissue and encourages rapid repair of damaged tissue.
 Borage Oil- Regenerates new skin cells and nourishes and hydrates
 Hemp Seed Oil- Aids in healing, inflammation and restores moisture
 Jojoba Oil- A highly penetrative oil which closely resembles the skin's natural sebum. Anti-inflammatory and has natural anti-oxidant properties.
 Rosemary and Lavender essential oils- Soothing, natural antibiotic healing properties

TATT SPLATT:
Specially formulated for use on newly tattooed skin. It's easily absorbed and has a calming yet non-overpowering scent, making it the perfect post tattoo balm for everyone. Tatt Splatt contains high quality ingredients that have been specifically chosen for their individual skin soothing properties, with each one highly beneficial to the skin. TATTOO AFTER CARE Apply a thin layer of Tatt Splatt to your new tattoo, 3 to 4 times daily for 7 - 10 days. Consult your tattooist prior to application
